## v1.1.0 (2026-06-02) — Wait-for-merge + honest exit-gate partition

**Changed by:** ProjectMnemosyne `/learn` AMEND workflow
**Verification:** verified-ci (ProjectHephaestus PR #876 merged; new gate language
appeared in a real ecosystem-run's production logs this session)

### What changed
Amended the existing `drive_prs_green` CI-driver skill with the NEXT fix on the same
driver. v1.0.0's Guard 4 was too blunt: it exited `rc=1` whenever ANY open PR remained,
even when every PR was `auto-merge=armed` and merging on its own. A real ecosystem run
marked **7 of 15 repos FAILED** with zero actual driver crashes.

Added (ProjectHephaestus PR #876, `hephaestus/automation/ci_driver.py`):

- **`_wait_for_pr_terminal(issue, pr) -> MERGED|CLOSED|FAILING|TIMEOUT`** — bounded
  exponential backoff (`min(2**n, 60)` cap, `HEPH_PR_MERGE_MAX_WAIT` default 1800s);
  reacts immediately to a required check concluding `failure` after arming. Wired into
  `_drive_issue` post-arm and into the still-OPEN branch of
  `_check_arming_on_drive_start`. `FAILING` → `_attempt_ci_fixes`; `MERGED` → fire
  post-merge `/learn` once.
- **Robust Dependabot arming** — `_enable_auto_merge(pr, is_bot_pr=False)` retries
  `gh pr merge --auto` (no `--squash`) for bot PRs on squash failure.
- **Honest exit gate** — `_evaluate_run_result()` partitions open PRs into
  `armed_pending` (truthy `autoMergeRequest` → WARNING, not a failure) vs `needs_action`
  (falsy → rc=1). New log lines: `"N PR(s) armed and still merging (waited; not a
  failure)"` and `"Repo not done: N open PR(s) need manual action"`.
- **No-commit hardening** — `_retry_no_commit_once(..., max_retries=2)` re-engages the
  agent up to twice (bounded) before recording the forensics marker. `max_fix_iterations`
  left unchanged.

Frontmatter: version `1.0.0` → `1.1.0`, date `2026-05-31` → `2026-06-02`, added `history`
field, added tags `wait-for-merge`, `auto-merge-armed`, `dependabot-arming`. Added a
v1.1.0 sub-section to Verified Workflow (steps 6–9), four new Failed Attempts rows, and
new PR/Verified-On/References entries for PR #876.

### Why
The user rejected "exit 0 on any armed PR" in favor of "actually WAIT until the PR
finishes (merge or fail) so the driver can react to failures/conflicts". The wait loop is
the correct design, not early-exit.

### Production verification (verified-ci)
A follow-up ecosystem run on the new build: ProjectNestor flipped FAILED→complete;
ProjectOdyssey waited 1743s then logged `"PR #5487 still OPEN after 1743s (limit 1800s);
leaving armed and pending"` and `"3 PR(s) armed and still merging (waited; not a
failure)"`, failing on only 1 genuine `needs_action` PR instead of the old 4; the
no-commit retry landed fixes on 5 PRs the old code abandoned.

### Known limitation (future enhancement)
An `auto-merge armed` PR with `mergeStateStatus == DIRTY` (merge conflict) sits OPEN
forever; `_wait_for_pr_terminal` returns `TIMEOUT` and makes no progress. Detect `DIRTY`
in the wait loop and re-trigger a mechanical rebase instead of waiting out 1800s.

